CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 4, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "6th Prize - Little Estelle Moyer, 7-month-old daughter of Mrs. Mary Lou Moyer, 323 Perry Street, McKeesport, who weighs 20 pounds and is 26-inches tall, was the winner of the sixth prize of $25. The baby, one of the few white children to be entered in contest, walked off with one of the major prizes."
TitMainTitle: John Ruffing Jr. presenting sixth prize to Joan Estelle Moyer, daughter of Mary Lou Moyer, in Centre Avenue YMCA during Carnation Milk baby contest
